Design Co | de-zi-ne co |
At Design Co, we envision creating an inclusive design community for the students through hands-on workshops, fun design competitions, and industry partnered events. Previous companies that have partnered with us include Facebook, BASIC Agency, Lyft, Intuit, and more.
Design Co
Largest pre-professional Design organization at UC San Diego that connects the community on campus with the finest industries.

© 2020 Lil Adam X
As a Web Developer on the team, I am currently working on optimizing and updating the Design Co Community page. This project was a cool initiative created by our amazing team. (Lucy, Alison, Paridhi) It is essentially an online catalog for students designers and alumni to connect as well as a platform for students to be discovered by potential recruiters. The site boasts a large list of talented designers, which are categorized according to their specializations. Check it out here.

Creative Team
here.
Why Did I Join
I’ve always been an active general member of Design Co. On Wednesdays, after fencing practice, I head straight to H&SS 1334 classrooms where it’s at. I made it a commitment to attend every single meeting because the organization fostered a conducive environment unlike any other where anyone who attends regardless of skill level was welcomed. It was very beautiful to see how the members cared for other aspiring designers and this resonated with one of the reasons why I became a designer.
Easy Decision
On January 14th, 2020, I received an update for my application for the Design Co Fellowship program. I had been accepted to participate in Design Co’s annual Bay Area Trip where we had the chance to visit companies such as Instagram, IDEO, Square, Uber, Figma, and Workday.

I was very touched by the hospitality received from all the companies we visited. The people who hosted us at the different companies were very genuine and helpful in giving us insights about their work culture as well as placing hope for us to be better designers. Hearing multiple perspectives from the people who have worked at a smaller scale to bigger scale companies shows that there is a place for everyone to succeed and enjoy what they are doing, no matter where they decide to put their design practices to work.
On March 6th, 2020, I applied and had been officially accepted to Design Co’s board. I can’t wait to share the exciting adventure that I will be a part of.
To Infinity and Beyond
If you want to get involved and know more about Design Co, feel free to reach out to me or anyone from our team. We’d be delighted to have you onboard our journey.
